{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01124w7D2BLiT8ZEnoKtB3HG","type":"tool_result","content":"  1070→### Task 9: Update Run model for concurrent steps\n  1071→\n  1072→**Files:**\n  1073→- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n  1074→\n  1075→**Step 1: Replace `CurrentStep` with `ActiveSteps`**\n  1076→\n  1077→Change the `Run` struct:\n  1078→\n  1079→```go\n  1080→type Run struct {\n  1081→\tID             string\n  1082→\tWorkflowName   string\n  1083→\tState          RunState\n  1084→\tActiveSteps    []string  // replaces CurrentStep\n  1085→\tStepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  1086→\tStartedAt      time.Time\n  1087→\tCompletedAt    time.Time\n  1088→}\n  1089→```\n  1090→\n  1091→Update `RecordStepStart` to append to `ActiveSteps` instead of overwriting `CurrentStep`. Update `RecordStepComplete` to remove from `ActiveSteps`.\n  1092→\n  1093→**Step 2: Verify it compiles and tests pass**\n  1094→\n  1095→Run: `go test ./... 2>&1 | tail -20`\n  1096→\n  1097→Fix any compilation errors from callers that reference `CurrentStep` (likely the engine and runner). Update them to use `ActiveSteps`.\n  1098→\n  1099→**Step 3: Commit**\n  1100→\n  1101→```bash\n  1102→git add internal/domain/run.go\n  1103→git commit -m \"feat(domain): replace CurrentStep with ActiveSteps for concurrency\"\n  1104→```\n  1105→\n  1106→---\n  1107→\n  1108→### Task 10: Update runner and status reporting\n  1109→\n  1110→**Files:**\n  1111→- Modify: `internal/agent/runner.go`\n  1112→\n  1113→**Step 1: Verify runner compiles with new engine API**\n  1114→\n  1115→The runner creates the engine and calls `eng.Run()`. The engine's API (`Run(ctx, wf)`) hasn't changed — the concurrency is internal. The `stepExecutor` and `statusReporter` interfaces are unchanged.\n  1116→\n  1117→Run: `go build ./internal/agent/...`\n  1118→Expected: success. If `CurrentStep` was referenced, update to `ActiveSteps`.\n  1119→\n  1120→**Step 2: Run full test suite**\n  1121→\n  1122→Run: `go test ./... -v 2>&1 | tail -40`\n  1123→Expected: all PASS.\n  1124→\n  1125→**Step 3: Commit if any changes were needed**\n  1126→\n  1127→```bash\n  1128→git add internal/agent/runner.go\n  1129→git commit -m \"fix(runner): adapt to concurrent engine and ActiveSteps\"\n  1130→```\n  1131→\n  1132→---\n  1133→\n  1134→### Task 11: Update example workflows\n  1135→\n  1136→**Files:**\n  1137→- Modify: `examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`\n  1138→- Modify: `examples/hello-world/build.cloche` (if it uses `pass`)\n  1139→- Modify: `examples/hello-world/flaky.cloche` (if it uses `pass`)\n  1140→\n  1141→**Step 1: Update ruby-calculator**\n  1142→\n  1143→Change `results = [pass, fail]` to `results = [success, fail]` in `test` and `lint` steps. Update wiring from `test:pass` → `test:success` and `lint:pass` → `lint:success`. Change `fix` step results from `[fixed, give-up]` to `[success, fail, give-up]` (or keep custom names — the prompt adapter will emit markers). Actually, keep `[fixed, give-up]` since those are custom edges that require markers.\n  1144→\n  1145→Wait — the fix step currently returns `\"fixed\"` via `resultOrDefault` (exit 0, first result). With the new protocol, exit 0 = `\"success\"`, which isn't declared. The fix step needs updating. Options:\n  1146→- Change results to `[success, fail, give-up]` and wiring to `fix:success -> test`.\n  1147→- Or have the prompt inject result instructions so the LLM emits `CLOCHE_RESULT:fixed`.\n  1148→\n  1149→The cleaner approach: rename to `[success, fail, give-up]` since `\"fixed\"` was just a synonym for success. Update wiring accordingly.\n  1150→\n  1151→```\n  1152→step fix {\n  1153→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n  1154→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n  1155→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  1156→}\n  1157→\n  1158→fix:success -> test\n  1159→fix:fail -> abort\n  1160→fix:give-up -> abort\n  1161→```\n  1162→\n  1163→Similarly, `implement` step: change from `[success, fail]` — these already match convention.\n  1164→\n  1165→**Step 2: Update hello-world workflows if needed**\n  1166→\n  1167→Check `build.cloche` and `flaky.cloche` for `pass` results and update.\n  1168→\n  1169→**Step 3: Run the DSL parser on updated files to verify**"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jkvrg5DQnwms7p32h2LiZt","session_id":"ba5bc30d-1b57-42d1-a8db-100c4b86f5e1","uuid":"054344b9-d659-4b86-b1d9-f1233bfc5223"}
