s 91-103)\n   - Documents environment variables injected into host workflow steps\n   - Line 97: Documents `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` variable\n   - Line 175: References how TaskID flows through orchestration\n\n### Current Run Struct Fields (from `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\nThe actual implementation now includes:\n- **TaskID** (line 47) - optional task ID this run is associated with\n- **ParentRunID** (line 46) - ID of parent (host) run\n- **IsHost** (line 45) - whether this is a host workflow run\n- **Title** (line 44) - one-line summary\n- **ContainerKept** (line 43) - whether container was retained\n- **BaseSHA** (line 42) - git HEAD at run start\n- **ContainerID** (line 41) - Docker container ID\n- **ErrorMessage** (line 40) - error description\n- **ProjectDir** (line 39) - project directory path\n- **CompletedAt**, **StartedAt** - timestamps\n- **StepExecutions** - list of step execution records\n- **ActiveSteps** - list of currently active step names (array, not single string)\n- **State** - run state (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- **WorkflowName** - workflow being executed\n- **ID** - run identifier\n\n### Documentation Updates Needed\n\nThe following documents should be reviewed and updated for accuracy:\n\n1. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`** - Mark as superseded or update Run struct definition\n2. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`** - Verify API response JSON examples include new Run fields if returned\n3. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md`** - Verify health calculation logic accounts for run state/grouping\n4. **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`** - Verify TaskID environment variable documentation is complete\n5. **`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`** - Verify task-related orchestration documentation is current\n6. **`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`** - Add inline documentation to the TaskID, ParentRunID, and IsHost fields explaining their usage"}],"totalDuratio