{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014r8CK5sseaWbEYWvzUoczG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Project Pages Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \"View Runs\" link. There is no\n     9→dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\n    10→or buried in other views.\n    11→\n    12→## Goal\n    13→\n    14→Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\n    15→\n    16→1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n    17→2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n    18→3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n    19→\n    20→## Route\n    21→\n    22→```\n    23→GET /projects/{name}\n    24→```\n    25→\n    26→`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\n    27→The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\n    28→\n    29→Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\n    30→`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\n    31→and a \"View all runs\" link to the filtered runs list.\n    32→\n    33→## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\n    34→\n    35→### Display\n    36→- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\n    37→- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\n    38→- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\n    39→\n    40→### API additions\n    41→\n    42→```\n    43→GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    44→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\n    45→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\n    46→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\"concurrency\": N}\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→`GET` response:\n    50→```json\n    51→{\n    52→  \"enabled\": true,\n    53→  \"in_flight\": 1,\n    54→  \"concurrency\": 2\n    55→}\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\n    59→`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\n    60→this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\n    61→\n    62→Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\n    63→\n    64→The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\n    65→interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\n    66→`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\n    67→\n    68→## Panel 2: Project Info\n    69→\n    70→### Display\n    71→- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\n    72→  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\n    73→- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\n    74→  design). Display as `v3`.\n    75→- **Prompt files**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show:\n    76→  - Current file contents in a collapsible accordion\n    77→  - Git commit history (short SHA, date, message)\n    78→  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\n    79→\n    80→### API additions\n    81→\n    82→```\n    83→GET /api/projects/{name}/info\n    84→```\n    85→\n    86→Response:\n    87→```json\n    88→{\n    89→  \"docker_image\": \"ubuntu:24.04\",\n    90→  \"version\": 3,\n    91→  \"prompt_files\": [\n    92→    {\n    93→      \"path\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\",\n    94→      \"content\": \"Full text of the prompt file...\",\n    95→      \"history\": [\n    96→        {\"sha\": \"abc1234\", \"date\": \"2026-03-05\", \"message\": \"evolution: tighten scope\"},\n    97→        {\"sha\": \"def5678\", \"date\": \"2026-03-01\", \"message\": \"init\"}\n    98→      ]\n    99→    }\n   100→  ]\n   101→}\n   102→```\n   103→\n   104→Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\n   105→via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\n   106→\n   107→```\n   108→GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\n   109→```\n   110→\n   111→Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\n   112→\n   113→## Panel 3: Workflow View\n   114→\n   115→### Display\n   116→- Two-level tab navigation:\n   117→  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   118→  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   119→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   120→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n   121→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   122→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   123→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   124→  - Step name and type\n   125→  - Results list\n   126→  - `max_attempts` if set\n   127→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n   128→  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n   129→  - For host script steps: the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\n   130→  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n   131→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n   132→\n   133→### DAG rendering\n   134→Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n   135→layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n   136→heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n   137→left-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n   138→\n   139→When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\n   140→collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\n   141→which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\n   142→grow in complexity.\n   143→\n   144→The DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n   145→\n   146→### API additions\n   147→\n   148→```\n   149→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n   150→```\n   151→\n   152→Response:\n   153→```json\n   154→[\n   155→  {\n   156→    \"name\": \"develop\",\n   157→    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n   158→    \"location\": \"container\",\n   159→    \"steps\": [\n   160→      {\n   161→        \"name\": \"implement\",\n   162→        \"type\": \"agent\",\n   163→        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n   164→        \"config\": {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\", \"max_attempts\": null}\n   165→      },\n   166→      ...\n   167→    ],\n   168→    \"wires\": [\n   169→      {\"from\": \"implement\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"test\"},\n   170→      ...\n   171→    ],\n   172→    \"entry_step\": \"implement\"\n   173→  }\n   174→]\n   175→```\n   176→\n   177→The `location` field is either `\"container\"` or `\"host\"`. Host workflows are parsed from\n   178→`.cloche/host.cloche` and included in the same response.\n   179→\n   180→```\n   181→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n   182→```\n   183→\n   184→Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\n   185→If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\n   186→\n   187→## Template / file changes\n   188→\n   189→- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n   190→- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\"project_detail\"`\n   191→- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\n   192→- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\n   193→\n   194→## Not in scope\n   195→\n   196→- Editing workflow files from the UI\n   197→- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\n   198→- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\n   199→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba5bc30d-1b57-42d1-a8db-100c4b86f5e1","uuid":"c260cccb-9a83-4696-ad9f-164866738c9a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md","content":"# Project Pages Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nThe projects landing page shows only health dots and a \"View Runs\" link. There is no\ndedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\nor buried in other views.\n\n## Goal\n\nAdd a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\n\n1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n\n## Route\n\n```\nGET /projects/{name}\n```\n\n`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\nThe handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\n\nProject cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\n`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\nand a \"View all runs\" link to the filtered runs list.\n\n## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\n\n### Display\n- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\n- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\n- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\"concurrency\": N}\n```\n\n`GET` response:\n```json\n{\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"in_flight\": 1,\n  \"concurrency\": 2\n}\n```\n\nThe orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\n`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\nthis flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\n\nConcurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\n\nThe Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\ninterface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\n`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\n\n## Panel 2: Project Info\n\n### Display\n- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\n  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\n- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\n  design). Display as `v3`.\n- **Prompt files**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show:\n  - Current file contents in a collapsible accordion\n  - Git commit history (short SHA, date, message)\n  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n{\n  \"docker_image\": \"ubuntu:24.04\",\n  \"version\": 3,\n  \"prompt_files\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\",\n      \"content\": \"Full text of the prompt file...\",\n      \"history\": [\n        {\"sha\": \"abc1234\", \"date\": \"2026-03-05\", \"message\": \"evolution: tighten scope\"},\n        {\"sha\": \"def5678\", \"date\": \"2026-03-01\", \"message\": \"init\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nImplementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\nvia `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\n```\n\nReturns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\n\n## Panel 3: Workflow View\n\n### Display\n- Two-level tab navigation:\n  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n  - Step name and type\n  - Results list\n  - `max_attempts` if set\n  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n  - For host script steps: the `run` command string or contents of the referenced file\n  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n\n### DAG rendering\nClient-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\nlayers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\nheuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\nleft-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n\nWhen multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ncollector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\nwhich feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\ngrow in complexity.\n\nThe DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"develop\",\n    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n    \"location\": \"container\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"implement\",\n        \"type\": \"agent\",\n        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],\n        \"config\": {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\", \"max_attempts\": null}\n      },\n      ...\n    ],\n    \"wires\": [\n      {\"from\": \"implement\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"test\"},\n      ...\n    ],\n    \"entry_step\": \"implement\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nThe `location` field is either `\"container\"` or `\"host\"`. Host workflows are parsed from\n`.cloche/host.cloche` and included in the same response.\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n```\n\nReturns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\nIf the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\n\n## Template / file changes\n\n- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\n- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\"project_detail\"`\n- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\n- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\n\n## Not in scope\n\n- Editing workflow files from the UI\n- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\n- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\n","numLines":199,"startLine":1,"totalLines":199}}}
