{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BCBfjarLXPhLkhj7avYUbr","type":"tool_result","content":"diff --git a/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css b/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\nindex 0794bfd..c6e6032 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\n@@ -572,6 +572,16 @@ details pre {\n /* Orchestrator status */\n .orch-status { font-size: 0.9rem; }\n \n+/* Task grouping header */\n+.run-task-header td {\n+    font-weight: 600;\n+    background: var(--bg-secondary);\n+    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);\n+    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;\n+    color: var(--text);\n+    font-size: 0.9rem;\n+}\n+\n /* Run tree grouping */\n .run-parent-row { opacity: 0.7; }\n .run-parent-row td:first-child { font-weight: 600; }\ndiff --git a/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html b/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\nindex 9ec4076..9acc22e 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\n@@ -17,6 +17,12 @@\n     <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"project-info\">Loading...</div>\n </div>\n \n+<!-- Panel 2: Tasks -->\n+<div class=\"panel\" id=\"tasks-panel\">\n+    <div class=\"panel-header\">Tasks</div>\n+    <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"tasks-body\">Loading...</div>\n+</div>\n+\n <!-- Panel 3: Workflow View -->\n <div class=\"panel\" id=\"workflow-panel\">\n     <div class=\"panel-header\">Workflows</div>\n@@ -462,8 +468,45 @@ window.deleteAllContainers = function() {\n         });\n };\n \n+function escapeHtml(s) {\n+    var d = document.createElement('div');\n+    d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n+    return d.innerHTML;\n+}\n+\n+function loadTasks() {\n+    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/tasks')\n+        .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n+        .then(function(tasks) {\n+            var body = document.getElementById('tasks-body');\n+            if (!tasks || tasks.length === 0) {\n+                body.innerHTML = '<p class=\"empty\">No tasks discovered</p>';\n+                return;\n+            }\n+            var html = '<table class=\"runs-table\" style=\"margin:0\"><thead><tr>';\n+            html += '<th>Task ID</th><th>Title</th><th>Status</th><th>Assigned</th><th>Run</th>';\n+            html += '</tr></thead><tbody>';\n+            for (var i = 0; i < tasks.length; i++) {\n+                var t = tasks[i];\n+                var statusClass = t.status === 'open' ? 'running' : (t.status === 'closed' ? 'succeeded' : 'pending');\n+                html += '<tr>';\n+                html += '<td class=\"mono\">' + escapeHtml(t.id) + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + escapeHtml(t.title || '') + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td><span class=\"badge badge-' + statusClass + '\">' + escapeHtml(t.status) + '</span></td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + (t.assigned ? 'Yes' : 'No') + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + (t.run_id ? '<a href=\"/runs/' + escapeHtml(t.run_id) + '\">' + escapeHtml(t.run_id) + '</a>' : '') + '</td>';\n+                html += '</tr>';\n+            }\n+            html += '</tbody></table>';\n+            body.innerHTML = html;\n+        })\n+        .catch(function() {});\n+}\n+\n // Load all panels\n loadProjectInfo();\n loadWorkflows();\n+loadTasks();\n+setInterval(loadTasks, 5000);\n </script>\n {{end}}\ndiff --git a/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html b/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\nindex 248c9f3..027c34f 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\n@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@\n     <tbody id=\"runs-body\">\n     {{if .Runs}}\n         {{range .Runs}}\n+        {{if ne .WorkflowName \"list-tasks\"}}\n         <tr class=\"{{if .ParentRunID}}run-child-row{{else if .IsHost}}run-parent-row{{end}}\">\n             <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n             <td>{{truncate .Title 50}}</td>\n@@ -43,6 +44,7 @@\n             <td class=\"error-cell\">{{truncate .ErrorMessage 80}}</td>\n         </tr>\n         {{end}}\n+        {{end}}\n     {{else}}\n         <tr><td colspan=\"9\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>\n     {{end}}\n@@ -82,9 +84,19 @@\n             });\n     };\n \n-    // groupRuns arranges runs so children appear directly after their parent.\n-    // Parents are de-emphasized; children (where active work happens) are prominent.\n+    // groupRuns arranges runs by task, then by parent-child within each task.\n+    // list-tasks runs are excluded. Runs with the same task_id are grouped\n+    // under a task header row. Runs without a task_id appear ungrouped.\n     function groupRuns(runs) {\n+        // Filter out list-tasks runs\n+        var filtered = [];\n+        for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n+            if (runs[i].workflow_name !== 'list-tasks') {\n+                filtered.push(runs[i]);\n+            }\n+        }\n+        runs = filtered;\n+\n         var parentMap = {};  // parent_run_id -> [children]\n         var topLevel = [];\n         var byId = {};\n@@ -111,15 +123,55 @@\n             return (b.started_at || '').localeCompare(a.started_at || '');\n         });\n \n-        var result = [];\n+        // Group top-level runs by task_id (preserving sort order within groups)\n+        var taskGroups = {};   // task_id -> [top-level runs]\n+        var taskOrder = [];    // ordered list of task_ids as first seen\n+        var ungrouped = [];    // runs without a task_id\n+\n         for (var i = 0; i < topLevel.length; i++) {\n             var r = topLevel[i];\n+            var tid = r.task_id || '';\n+            if (tid) {\n+                if (!taskGroups[tid]) {\n+                    taskGroups[tid] = [];\n+                    taskOrder.push(tid);\n+                }\n+                taskGroups[tid].push(r);\n+            } else {\n+                ungrouped.push(r);\n+            }\n+        }\n+\n+        var result = [];\n+\n+        // Emit task groups first (they have active context)\n+        for (var ti = 0; ti < taskOrder.length; ti++) {\n+            var tid = taskOrder[ti];\n+            var group = taskGroups[tid];\n+            // Task header row\n+            result.push({ run: null, isParent: false, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: true, taskID: tid });\n+            for (var gi = 0; gi < group.length; gi++) {\n+                var r = group[gi];\n+                var children = parentMap[r.id];\n+                var isParent = children && children.length > 0;\n+                result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n+                if (children) {\n+                    for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++) {\n+                        result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n+                    }\n+                }\n+            }\n+        }\n+\n+        // Emit ungrouped runs\n+        for (var i = 0; i < ungrouped.length; i++) {\n+            var r = ungrouped[i];\n             var children = parentMap[r.id];\n             var isParent = children && children.length > 0;\n-            result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false });\n+            result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n             if (children) {\n                 for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++) {\n-                    result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true });\n+                    result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n                 }\n             }\n         }\n@@ -128,7 +180,7 @@\n         for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n             var r = runs[i];\n             if (r.parent_run_id && !byId[r.parent_run_id]) {\n-                result.push({ run: r, isParent: false, isChild: true });\n+                result.push({ run: r, isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n             }\n         }\n \n@@ -150,9 +202,23 @@\n                 }\n \n                 var grouped = groupRuns(runs);\n+                // Check if all entries (after list-tasks filtering) are empty\n+                var hasRuns = false;\n+                for (var i = 0; i < grouped.length; i++) {\n+                    if (grouped[i].run) { hasRuns = true; break; }\n+                }\n+                if (!hasRuns && grouped.length === 0) {\n+                    tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"9\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>';\n+                    return;\n+                }\n+\n                 var html = '';\n                 for (var i = 0; i < grouped.length; i++) {\n                     var entry = grouped[i];\n+                    if (entry.isTaskHeader) {\n+                        html += '<tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: ' + escapeHtml(entry.taskID) + '</td></tr>';\n+                        continue;\n+                    }\n                     var r = entry.run;\n                     var cid = r.container_id || '';\n                     if (cid.length > 12) cid = cid.substring(0, 12);","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba5bc30d-1b57-42d1-a8db-100c4b86f5e1","uuid":"3e979e56-ef89-4004-9025-d350fd2af45f","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"diff --git a/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css b/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\nindex 0794bfd..c6e6032 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\n@@ -572,6 +572,16 @@ details pre {\n /* Orchestrator status */\n .orch-status { font-size: 0.9rem; }\n \n+/* Task grouping header */\n+.run-task-header td {\n+    font-weight: 600;\n+    background: var(--bg-secondary);\n+    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);\n+    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;\n+    color: var(--text);\n+    font-size: 0.9rem;\n+}\n+\n /* Run tree grouping */\n .run-parent-row { opacity: 0.7; }\n .run-parent-row td:first-child { font-weight: 600; }\ndiff --git a/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html b/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\nindex 9ec4076..9acc22e 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\n@@ -17,6 +17,12 @@\n     <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"project-info\">Loading...</div>\n </div>\n \n+<!-- Panel 2: Tasks -->\n+<div class=\"panel\" id=\"tasks-panel\">\n+    <div class=\"panel-header\">Tasks</div>\n+    <div class=\"panel-body\" id=\"tasks-body\">Loading...</div>\n+</div>\n+\n <!-- Panel 3: Workflow View -->\n <div class=\"panel\" id=\"workflow-panel\">\n     <div class=\"panel-header\">Workflows</div>\n@@ -462,8 +468,45 @@ window.deleteAllContainers = function() {\n         });\n };\n \n+function escapeHtml(s) {\n+    var d = document.createElement('div');\n+    d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n+    return d.innerHTML;\n+}\n+\n+function loadTasks() {\n+    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/tasks')\n+        .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n+        .then(function(tasks) {\n+            var body = document.getElementById('tasks-body');\n+            if (!tasks || tasks.length === 0) {\n+                body.innerHTML = '<p class=\"empty\">No tasks discovered</p>';\n+                return;\n+            }\n+            var html = '<table class=\"runs-table\" style=\"margin:0\"><thead><tr>';\n+            html += '<th>Task ID</th><th>Title</th><th>Status</th><th>Assigned</th><th>Run</th>';\n+            html += '</tr></thead><tbody>';\n+            for (var i = 0; i < tasks.length; i++) {\n+                var t = tasks[i];\n+                var statusClass = t.status === 'open' ? 'running' : (t.status === 'closed' ? 'succeeded' : 'pending');\n+                html += '<tr>';\n+                html += '<td class=\"mono\">' + escapeHtml(t.id) + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + escapeHtml(t.title || '') + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td><span class=\"badge badge-' + statusClass + '\">' + escapeHtml(t.status) + '</span></td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + (t.assigned ? 'Yes' : 'No') + '</td>';\n+                html += '<td>' + (t.run_id ? '<a href=\"/runs/' + escapeHtml(t.run_id) + '\">' + escapeHtml(t.run_id) + '</a>' : '') + '</td>';\n+                html += '</tr>';\n+            }\n+            html += '</tbody></table>';\n+            body.innerHTML = html;\n+        })\n+        .catch(function() {});\n+}\n+\n // Load all panels\n loadProjectInfo();\n loadWorkflows();\n+loadTasks();\n+setInterval(loadTasks, 5000);\n </script>\n {{end}}\ndiff --git a/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html b/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\nindex 248c9f3..027c34f 100644\n--- a/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\n+++ b/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\n@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@\n     <tbody id=\"runs-body\">\n     {{if .Runs}}\n         {{range .Runs}}\n+        {{if ne .WorkflowName \"list-tasks\"}}\n         <tr class=\"{{if .ParentRunID}}run-child-row{{else if .IsHost}}run-parent-row{{end}}\">\n             <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n             <td>{{truncate .Title 50}}</td>\n@@ -43,6 +44,7 @@\n             <td class=\"error-cell\">{{truncate .ErrorMessage 80}}</td>\n         </tr>\n         {{end}}\n+        {{end}}\n     {{else}}\n         <tr><td colspan=\"9\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>\n     {{end}}\n@@ -82,9 +84,19 @@\n             });\n     };\n \n-    // groupRuns arranges runs so children appear directly after their parent.\n-    // Parents are de-emphasized; children (where active work happens) are prominent.\n+    // groupRuns arranges runs by task, then by parent-child within each task.\n+    // list-tasks runs are excluded. Runs with the same task_id are grouped\n+    // under a task header row. Runs without a task_id appear ungrouped.\n     function groupRuns(runs) {\n+        // Filter out list-tasks runs\n+        var filtered = [];\n+        for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n+            if (runs[i].workflow_name !== 'list-tasks') {\n+                filtered.push(runs[i]);\n+            }\n+        }\n+        runs = filtered;\n+\n         var parentMap = {};  // parent_run_id -> [children]\n         var topLevel = [];\n         var byId = {};\n@@ -111,15 +123,55 @@\n             return (b.started_at || '').localeCompare(a.started_at || '');\n         });\n \n-        var result = [];\n+        // Group top-level runs by task_id (preserving sort order within groups)\n+        var taskGroups = {};   // task_id -> [top-level runs]\n+        var taskOrder = [];    // ordered list of task_ids as first seen\n+        var ungrouped = [];    // runs without a task_id\n+\n         for (var i = 0; i < topLevel.length; i++) {\n             var r = topLevel[i];\n+            var tid = r.task_id || '';\n+            if (tid) {\n+                if (!taskGroups[tid]) {\n+                    taskGroups[tid] = [];\n+                    taskOrder.push(tid);\n+                }\n+                taskGroups[tid].push(r);\n+            } else {\n+                ungrouped.push(r);\n+            }\n+        }\n+\n+        var result = [];\n+\n+        // Emit task groups first (they have active context)\n+        for (var ti = 0; ti < taskOrder.length; ti++) {\n+            var tid = taskOrder[ti];\n+            var group = taskGroups[tid];\n+            // Task header row\n+            result.push({ run: null, isParent: false, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: true, taskID: tid });\n+            for (var gi = 0; gi < group.length; gi++) {\n+                var r = group[gi];\n+                var children = parentMap[r.id];\n+                var isParent = children && children.length > 0;\n+                result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n+                if (children) {\n+                    for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++) {\n+                        result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n+                    }\n+                }\n+            }\n+        }\n+\n+        // Emit ungrouped runs\n+        for (var i = 0; i < ungrouped.length; i++) {\n+            var r = ungrouped[i];\n             var children = parentMap[r.id];\n             var isParent = children && children.length > 0;\n-            result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false });\n+            result.push({ run: r, isParent: isParent, isChild: false, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n             if (children) {\n                 for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++) {\n-                    result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true });\n+                    result.push({ run: children[j], isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n                 }\n             }\n         }\n@@ -128,7 +180,7 @@\n         for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n             var r = runs[i];\n             if (r.parent_run_id && !byId[r.parent_run_id]) {\n-                result.push({ run: r, isParent: false, isChild: true });\n+                result.push({ run: r, isParent: false, isChild: true, isTaskHeader: false, taskID: '' });\n             }\n         }\n \n@@ -150,9 +202,23 @@\n                 }\n \n                 var grouped = groupRuns(runs);\n+                // Check if all entries (after list-tasks filtering) are empty\n+                var hasRuns = false;\n+                for (var i = 0; i < grouped.length; i++) {\n+                    if (grouped[i].run) { hasRuns = true; break; }\n+                }\n+                if (!hasRuns && grouped.length === 0) {\n+                    tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"9\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>';\n+                    return;\n+                }\n+\n                 var html = '';\n                 for (var i = 0; i < grouped.length; i++) {\n                     var entry = grouped[i];\n+                    if (entry.isTaskHeader) {\n+                        html += '<tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: ' + escapeHtml(entry.taskID) + '</td></tr>';\n+                        continue;\n+                    }\n                     var r = entry.run;\n                     var cid = r.container_id || '';\n                     if (cid.length > 12) cid = cid.substring(0, 12);","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LJBNkNyTTYCnCo2UUtvyUs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the code changes:\n\n1. **Domain**: `Run` struct gets a new `TaskID` field\n2. **SQLite store**: `task_id` column added to runs table, persisted in CRUD operations\n3. **Web API**: `apiRun` includes `task_id` in JSON responses\n4. **Runs page**: \n   - `list-tasks` runs are hidden from the HTML template and JS rendering\n   - Runs are grouped by `task_id` with task header rows\n   - CSS added for task group headers\n5. **Project detail page**: New \"Tasks\" panel added that loads from `/api/projects/{name}/tasks`\n\n\n6. **Host executor/runner**: `TaskID` is propagated from host runs to child container runs\n\nNow I'm checking which docs need updating. Looking at the existing documentation, most of it covers the CLI, workflow DSL, and execution model rather than the data model or web UI specifics. The `task_id` concept is already documented through the `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable, and since the docs don't describe the Run struct or web UI details, there's no update needed for the core documentation files.\n\nHowever, the project-pages-design.md is a design document that's now out of sync with the implementation. The original design specified three panels (Orchestrator, Project Info, Workflow View), but the code now includes a fourth Tasks panel. Since the update-docs task explicitly asks to compare source code changes against documentation and update sections that are actually out of date, this design doc should be revised to reflect the current implementation.\n\nLet me scan through the remaining documentation to see if there are any other files that reference the web UI structure or the Run API that might also need updating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3212,"cache_read_inp